pageContext.claim: “We just had a vote today, that was a lopsided vote in favor of -- that's the end of impeachment.”
pageContext.analysis: The Democratic-controlled House voted down an impeachment resolution, but that's not "the end of impeachment." In fact, the House Judiciary Committee has begun an impeachment inquiry and Democrats have said in a court filing that the panel "is now determining whether to recommend articles of impeachment against the President based on the obstructive conduct described by the Special Counsel.”
